-I-Turned-Pretty-Season-Three-Tease-Art.jpg?resize=285,356 285w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Summer-I-Turned-Pretty-Season-Three-Tease-Art.jpg?resize=614,768 614w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Summer-I-Turned-Pretty-Season-Three-Tease-Art.jpg?resize=1024,1280 1024w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 819px) 100vw, 819px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe series, based on creator/showrunner Jenny Han’s book trilogy, revolves around the love triangle between 16-year-old Isabel “Belly” Conklin (played by Lola Tung) and the Fisher brothers, broody Conrad (Christopher Briney) and easygoing Jeremiah (Gavin Casalegno), with whom Belly has grown up. The upcoming season will chronicle the events of Han’s third (and final) book, \u003cem\u003eWe’ll Always Have Summer\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the Season 2 finale, which dropped August 18, 2023, Belly released Conrad from her heart and began a relationship with Jeremiah. Reflecting on Belly decision, star \u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/interviews/the-summer-i-turned-pretty-recap-season-2-finale-episode-8-belly-jeremiah-conrad-love-triangle-1235026222/\"\u003eLola Tung told TVLine\u003c/a\u003e, “I think that her choice made sense for her in the moment. She’s been through a lot with both of them, and I think she’s realized that, at that time, Conrad has not shown her that he will ever be willing to fight for that relationship as much as she will.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“Here’s Jeremiah, ready to fight for her, continuing to fight for her, just proving, I think, constantly how much he loves her and cares about her, even in watching her be with Conrad for so long,” Tung continued, adding that Jeremiah “is the person that she is falling in love with” at the moment.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn Season 3, “it’s the end of her junior year of college, and Belly’s looking forward to another summer in Cousins with her soulmate, Jeremiah,” reads the official synopsis. “Her future seems set, until some core-shaking events bring her first love Conrad back into her life. Now on the brink of adulthood, Belly finds herself at a crossroads and must decide which brother has her heart. Summer will never be the same…”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs for whether fans can expect the final season to follow the last book and end with [spoiler], “there are going to be surprises,” Han told \u003ca rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://ew.com/the-summer-i-turned-pretty-final-season-first-look-surprises-exclusive-11703879\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eEntertainment Weekly\u003c/a\u003e. “There are the things that they know and then there are things they think they know, and then there’s going to be, hopefully, things that surprise them.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-component=\"linked-gallery\"\u003e\u003cfigure data-component=\"image\" data-alias=\"\" data-ratio=\"threeByTwo\" data-round=\"false\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\" alt=\"Courtesy of Everett Collection (x2); Prime Video; The CW\" height=\"840\" width=\"1240\" srcset=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1 1240w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=200%2C135 200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=300%2C203 300w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=768%2C520 768w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1024%2C694 1024w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/best-teen-dramas.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026